description: Returns a list of one or more conformance packs.

parameters.name: ConformancePackNames
parameters.description: Comma-separated list of conformance pack names for which you want details. If you do not specify any names, Config returns details for all your conformance packs. (string) ---

nested_items.name: ConformancePackDetails
nested_items.description: Returns a list of ConformancePackDetail objects.

nested_items.name: ConformancePackArn
nested_items.description: Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the conformance pack.

nested_items.name: DeliveryS3Bucket
nested_items.description: The name of the Amazon S3 bucket where Config stores conformance pack templates.

nested_items.name: DeliveryS3KeyPrefix
nested_items.description: The prefix for the Amazon S3 bucket.

nested_items.name: ParameterName
nested_items.description: One part of a key-value pair.

nested_items.name: ParameterValue
nested_items.description: Another part of the key-value pair.

nested_items.name: LastUpdateRequestedTime
nested_items.description: The last time a conformation pack update was requested.

nested_items.name: CreatedBy
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services service that created the conformance pack.

nested_items.name: TemplateSSMDocumentDetails
nested_items.description: An object that contains the name or Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Amazon Web Services Systems Manager document (SSM document) and the version of the SSM document that is used to create a conformance pack.

nested_items.name: DocumentName
nested_items.description: The name or Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the SSM document to use to create a conformance pack. If you use the document name, Config checks only your account and Amazon Web Services Region for the SSM document.

nested_items.name: DocumentVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the SSM document to use to create a conformance pack. By default, Config uses the latest version.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The nextToken string returned in a previous request that you use to request the next page of results in a paginated response.
